We’re going to look at some sample data from Texas on housing prices throughout the state.
First we’ll load data.


Code
# run this line below load the data for this assignment
# we'll use a built-in dataset from the ggplot2 package (loaded as party of the tidyverse)
housesales <- ggplot2::txhousing

title: Nuria Diaz Munoz
text: Hi, I’m Nuria Diaz, a junior at the George Washington University studying journalism and mass communcaition. I’m interested in foreign correspondence and investigative journalism, in the past three years I have worked at NBC4, C-SPAN and PolitiFact. My hobbies are reading, writing and watching sports during my free time.
